The paper presents an online learning algorithm for solving combinatorial network optimization problems with stochastic edge weights that vary as independent Markov chains with unknown dynamics. This involves techniques from machine learning (online learning) and combinatorial optimization (network optimization). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
